<exercise xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.0">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Suppose that there is a function <m>g</m> such that <m>g({{base}}) = {{baseval}}</m> and <m>g({{increment}}) = {{incrementval}}</m>. Use these values to estimate <m>g'({{base}})</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>
            g'({{base}}) \approx \frac{ g({{increment}}) - g({{base}}) }{ ({{increment}}) - ({{base}}) } = 
            \frac{ ({{incrementval}}) - ({{baseval}}) }{ ({{increment}}) - ({{base}}) } = {{secantslope}}
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>